About Me

I’m a driven professional with a strong background in leadership and project management, currently transitioning from the military into the engineering field. With experience in managing complex operations and spearheading special projects, I’ve also developed technical skills in programming, embedded systems, and web development.

In my free time, I enjoy building machine learning models to predict NFL games and creating websites for family recipes. I hold a secret clearance and am excited to apply my problem-solving abilities in a new engineering career. In my free time, I love to run, play chess, and hike or climb outdoors as much as possible.
